## Public Member Functions

### getExternalRedirect() {#a124bbf0bcca319d0cad7086bc6091e29}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>std::optional&lt; StringRef &gt; llvm::vfs::RedirectingFileSystem::LookupResult::getExternalRedirect () const</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
If the found <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vfs/redirectingfilesystem/entry">Entry</a> maps the input path to a path in the external file system (i.e.

it is a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vfs/redirectingfilesystem/fileentry">FileEntry</a> or <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vfs/redirectingfilesystem/directoryremapentry">DirectoryRemapEntry</a>), returns that path.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/virtualfilesystem-h/#l00931">931</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/virtualfilesystem-h">VirtualFileSystem.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### getPath() {#aaaa3106261fa4af53b07b638d39a1ae3}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void RedirectingFileSystem::LookupResult::getPath (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">llvm::SmallVectorImpl</a>&lt; char &gt; &amp; Path) const</>}>
Get the (canonical) path of the found entry.

This uses the as-written path components from the VFS specification.
